post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_29927695_29927766_0": {"length": 9, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 2665}}, "n3337": {"so_29927695_29927766_0": {"length": 9, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 2629}}, "n4659": {"so_29927695_29927766_0": {"length": 9, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 3405}}}, "29927766": {"Id": "29927766", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Section 30.2.4 [thread.req.timing] (more-or-less accurate version available at <a href=\"http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2010/n3128.html#thread.req.timing\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2010/n3128.html#thread.req.timing</a>) says:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_29927695_29927766_0\">if Ca &gt; Ct, the waiting function should wake as soon as possible, i.e.\n  Ca + Di + Dm, since the timeout is already satisfied.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So the answer to your question is \"yes\".</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2015-04-28T19:03:16.073", "CommentCount": "1", "CreationDate": "2015-04-28T19:03:16.073", "ParentId": "29927695", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "768469"}, "29927695": {"ViewCount": "115", "Body": "<p>I have a small question about using this method.\nWill my thread wake up if the <code>std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now()</code> is greater then the second parameter(<code>abs_time</code>)?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "29927766", "Title": "std::condition_variable::wait_until function", "CreationDate": "2015-04-28T18:58:12.323", "Id": "29927695", "CommentCount": "0", "LastEditDate": "2015-04-28T19:00:31.827", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "3953764", "LastActivityDate": "2015-04-28T19:03:16.073", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "3818229", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><condition-variable><stdthread>", "AnswerCount": "1"}});